    <sect1>
        <title>Summary</title>
        <para> This set of exercises comes in two parts. In the first, we'll look at adding a user
            model with authentication to our sample application, so you can restrict who's allowed
            to carry out certain actions. In the second part, we'll see what effect some common
            attacks have, and see how easy it is to protect against them. </para>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title>Setup</title>
        <para> Make sure you're up to date on the code we created in the last set of exercises. Go
            to your repository folder in a terminal window and type git checkout session_four to get
            all the code from session four. Copy this code, in the correct folders, across to your
            working folders. </para>
    </sect1>
